cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.IT

This paper is about Dynamic Adaptive Streaming over HTTP (DASH), which is a multimedia streaming technique. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with bandwidth allocation and rate adaptation, which are networking issues, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The paper proposes a non-cooperative game theory-based algorithm, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also considers Quality of Experience (QoE) of users, which is a user-centric metric, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a distributed iterative algorithm, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory).
